1.6   Planned changes to improve safety



The primary mechanisms to identify and plan safety improvements include (but are not limited to):

-  Process Hazard Analysis Studies including required updates;

-  Cal/ARP Seismic Assessment;

-  Compliance Audits;

-  Mechanical Integrity Program (Routine Inspections & Maintenance);

-  IIAR Bulletin 109 Inspections;

-  WPS Inspection Protocol



The programs above may result in recommendations ranging from capital improvements to routine maintenance. Where appropriate service calls are established in parallel to identified needs. Current planned changes to improve safety include recommendations as a result of the Process Hazard Analysis (PHA) performed 9/24/2019.  Recommendations have been compiled; reviewed by management, and a written implementation schedule has been prepared. The completion of recommendations is scheduled by 8/28/2020.  A summary includes maintenance items, mechanical validations and administrative/documentation improvements.
